summary: An FBI 302 interview report from August 7, 2019, documenting an interview with an unnamed individual at the NYPD's 13th Precinct in Long Island City, Queens. The individual denied knowing Jeffrey Epstein when shown his photo and provided a brief personal history of moving between Brazil, San Diego, and New York.

keyFacts: An individual was interviewed by the FBI on August 7, 2019, and denied knowing Jeffrey Epstein when shown his photo.
The interview took place at the NYPD's 13th Precinct in Long Island City, Queens, New York.
The individual provided a personal history involving moving from Brazil to the United States, living in San Diego, and returning to New York in 2005.
The document is an FBI 302 form, which is a report of investigation, and contains a standard disclaimer that it is FBI property and not for external distribution.
The name of the individual interviewed is redacted or not provided in the extracted text.
